title.narrative:
Research conducted on WB enterprise surveys in three target countries: Kenya, Uganda and Turkey. Research findings explore the critical nature of rights for WEE and the particular challenges faced by women entrepreneurs accessing rights, social protection, obtaining contracts, in registration, formalization and compliance, and the costs of violence and corruption for their enterprises.  The findings inform the development of key knowledge products identified below.

These will include a country report outlining the challenges identified by women entrepreneurs for operating and upscaling their businesses (3 country reports).  ICRW will have 4 policy briefs on the critical role of social protection, infrastructure and public services;

Quantity of knowledge products produced (report, blogs, op-eds, conference participation), social media activity reporting the discussions and coalition events, substantive engagement with institution representatives around knowledge products.
